Interpreting archival sources and taking into account results of folkloristic research, the changing worldview of Estonians will be analysed in a diachronic perspective.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide a folkloristic overview about the genesis of Estonian world-view.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students: - know the development of Estonian traditional culture; - know and understands the process of Estonian cultural lore as a cohesive whole from a traditional world-view to our contemporary society; - know the scientific tradition of researching folklore in Estonia, and can work on it in the case of further interest; - know Estonian traditional religion; - know Estonian traditional calendar; - know and can distinguish different forms of oral tradition; - understand the specific features of folklore process; - are related to cultural lore and can make use of it in their further creative work.
